My Recommendation for Deployment
Go with Solution 2 (Client-Side WAV Encoding) because:
✅ Works on any server (no external dependencies)
✅ Reduces server load (processing happens client-side)
✅ WAV is universally supported by all audio libraries
✅ Most reliable - no library version conflicts


Exactly right! Your optimization thinking is spot-on:
Current float approach:
44kHz × 60s = 2.64M samples
Each float as JSON string ≈ 12-15 bytes
Total: ~32-40 MB per minute ❌
Optimized int16 + base64:
Same 2.64M samples
int16 = 2 bytes per sample
Base64 encoded ≈ 2.67 bytes per sample
Total: ~7 MB per minute ✅
Or with downsampling to 16kHz:
16kHz × 60s = 960k samples
int16 + base64 ≈ 2.67 bytes per sample
Total: ~2.5 MB per minute ✅✅
So you could:
